---
import ElevationLayout from '../layouts/ElevationLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/elevation/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../components/elevation/Section.astro';
---

<ElevationLayout
  title="How We Build"
  description="Evoked builds governance architecture for AI. We also use AI to build it. Here's where we stand in the supply chain and why we build what we build anyway."
>
  <Hero
    eyebrowParts={["About", "How we build"]}
    headline="How we build."
    metaphor={["Evoked builds governance architecture for AI."]}
    sub="We also use AI to build it."
  />

  <Section marker="FIG · I" heading="What we use">
    <p class="lede">
      We use Claude by Anthropic. It is our AI infrastructure - development,
      analysis, agent operations. We are paying customers of Anthropic. We run
      on commercial infrastructure - Vercel, Railway, standard tools.
    </p>
    <p class="hwb-body">We are customers of the AI industry we critique.</p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · II" heading="What we don't do">
    <ul class="hwb-list">
      <li>We don't build foundation models</li>
      <li>We don't train on user data</li>
      <li>We don't employ data annotation labor</li>
      <li>We don't operate data centers</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="hwb-body">We don't extract. That's the line.</p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · III" heading="What we build instead">
    <p class="lede">
      <a class="hwb-link" href="/products">Governance frameworks</a>
      that any AI system can be held to. Sovereignty assessments that measure
      whether technology honors its users. Restraint specifications that define
      what agents must refuse. The architecture that tells the technology where
      to stop.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · IV" heading="The position">
    <p class="lede">
      The technology has utility. The political economy of its production is
      where the harm lives. We're trying to change the economy, not pretend the
      technology doesn't exist.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="NOTA · BENE" closing={true}>
    <p class="hwb-close">
      We evoke. We never extract. That applies to how we build, not just what
      we build.
    </p>
    <p class="hwb-see-also">
      See our <a class="hwb-link" href="/pledge">Defensive Patent Pledge</a>.
    </p>
  </Section>
</ElevationLayout>

<style>
  .hwb-body {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1rem + 0.3vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--el-text-deep);
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .hwb-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem) 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .hwb-list li {
    padding: 0.85rem 1.25rem;
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.2vw, 1.1rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--el-text-deep);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .hwb-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .hwb-link {
    color: var(--el-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .hwb-link:hover {
    color: var(--el-text-deep);
    border-color: var(--el-accent);
  }

  .hwb-close {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 1.05rem + 0.4vw, 1.35rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--el-text-deep);
    margin: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 1vw, 2rem) 0 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .hwb-see-also {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1vw, 2rem);
  }
</style>
